04/09/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A firefighter critically injured last week while battling a blaze on Kornati island died on Monday (September 3rd).
Seven other firefighters died there, trapped by the flames.
Three remain hospitalised in critical condition.
Prosecutors have charged a 20-year old employee of the Kornati National Park with starting the deadly blaze, by tossing a burning cigarette butt into dry grass.
(Vecernji List - 04/09/07;
HRT, RTRS, Javno, AP - 03/09/07)
